# node_todo
express, mongodb example

1.First to create an api you should have install node.js and mongoodb.
2.open the command prompt or terminal and go to the file directory.
3.Type "npm install" and let the npm do the remaining work.
4.After the installation is complete change the URL&user_name & password in the server.js file.
5.Then go to the terminal and type npm start.
6.The server will start on the port localhost:8888
